  "text": "Bleeding after pancreaticoduodenectomy is a fatal complication, and endovascular treatment is widely performed. Recently it has been reported that stent grafting is especially an appropriate treatment [CITATION_1] . Here, we present a rare complication of rebleeding developing 40 days after stent graft placement in the celiac artery.",
